If that's true, then this combination is invalid. So the code inside that if block should set isbad to true and break out of the loop or continue. So the code inside the if statement should be:

isbad = true;
break;

Because once any of the variables a, b, c has a bit higher than the corresponding bit in n (when they weren't allowed to be higher before), the entire combination is invalid and we can't proceed.
